C%20rather%20than%20taking%20anticipatory%20or%20preventive%20measures%2C%26quot%3B%20Kofman%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKofman%20believes%20the%20Russian%20airfields%20were%20hit%20by%20the%20cluster-bomb%20version%20of%20ATACMS%2C%20which%20only%20has%20a%20range%20of%20about%20100%20miles%20but%20is%20designed%20to%20%26quot%3Bdestroy%20manpower%2C%20equipment%2C%20material%20out%20in%20the%20open%2C%20and%20time-sensitive%20targets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20jets%20have%20played%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-air-force-largely-intact-has-operational-problems-in-ukraine-2023-7%5C%22%3Ea%20marginal%20role%20in%20the%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20kept%20at%20bay%20by%20Ukrainian%20air%20defenses.%20This%20has%20put%20the%20burden%20of%20air%20support%20on%20Russian%20attack%20helicopters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ukrainian%20strike%20brigades%2C%20equipped%20with%20Western-supplied%20armored%20vehicles%2C%20launched%20a%20counteroffensive%20in%20June%2C%20they%20suffered%20losses%20from%20Russian%20helicopters%20that%20picked%20off%20vehicles%20that%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F07%2F15%2Fukraine-war-russia-mines-counteroffensive%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estuck%20in%20minefields%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20had%20advanced%20beyond%20the%20range%20of%20Ukrainian%20air%20defenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221347%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Mi-24%20Mi-8%20helicopters%20Crimea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651c450642ecf94db476b051%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221010%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20Mi-24%20and%20Mi-8%20helicopters%20at%20a%20base%20in%20Crimea%20in%20April%202021.%3Cp%3EMaxar%20Technologies%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatacms-could-help-ukraine-attack-russian-helicopter-bases-2023-10%5C%22%3EKofman%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatacms-could-help-ukraine-attack-russian-helicopter-bases-2023-10%5C%22%3Eand%20other%20observers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20those%20helicopter%20bases%20were%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20most%20obvious%20targets%26quot%3B%20for%20Ukrainian%20ATACMS%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBases%20in%20Berdyansk%20and%20elsewhere%20in%20Luhansk%20%26quot%3Bare%20very%20well%20known%2C%20very%20well%20established%2C%20with%20revetments%20and%20helicopters%20dispersed%20across%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Kofman%20said%20on%20the%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20Ka-52s%20and%20Mi-28s%20have%20been%20flying%20from%20that%20have%20been%20a%20big%20issue%20for%20Ukrainian%20forces.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20about%20900%20helicopters%20that%20Russia's%20military%20had%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Frussia-helicopters-airfield-attack-ukraine-war-1835641%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%20one-third%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20been%20lost%20as%20of%20June%2C%20according%20to%20Ukraine's%20military.%20Even%20if%20those%20losses%20are%20exaggerated%20%E2%80%94%20and%20open-source%20trackers%20put%20the%20tally%20at%20a%20little%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oryxspioenkop.com%2F2022%2F02%2Fattack-on-europe-documenting-equipment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%20Russian%20130%20helicopters%3C%2Fa%3E%20lost%20or%20damaged%20%E2%80%94%20attack%20helicopters%20in%20particular%20are%20much%20too%20valuable%20to%20be%20left%20exposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20that%20Russian%20forces%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20been%20smacked%20by%20Western-supplied%20weapons.%20US-made%20Javelin%20and%20British-Swedish-designed%20NLAW%20anti-tank%20missiles%20wreaked%20havoc%20on%20Russian%20armored%20columns%20driving%20toward%20Kyiv%20in%20the%20opening%20days%20of%20the%20invasion%20in%20February%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20weeks%20after%20US-made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffighting-in-eastern-ukraine-showed-benefits-and-limitations-of-himars-2023-1%5C%22%3EHIMARS%20rockets%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20supplied%20in%20summer%202022%2C%20they%20destroyed%20Russian%20ammunition%20depots%20and%20command%20posts.%20British-made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-storm-shadow-effective-long-range-missile-but-russia-adapts-2023-7%5C%22%3EStorm%20Shadow%3C%2Fa%3E%20cruise%20missiles%2C%20supplied%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20have%20damaged%20vital%20bridges%20to%20Crimea%20and%20other%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.nv.ua%2Fnation%2Fukrainian-af-commander-hints-kalibr-missile-carrier-was-hit-with-storm-shadow-cruise-missiles-50365856.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evaluable%20hardware%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20peninsula.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20M142%20HIMARS%20Bakhmut%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a2e6636075be0019c28285%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221163%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20troops%20fire%20HIMARS%20rockets%20toward%20Bakhmut%20in%20May.%3Cp%3ESerhii%20Mykhalchuk%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20buzz%20about%20these%20wonder%20weapons%20and%20their%20initial%20impact%2C%20they%20soon%20lost%20much%20of%20their%20luster.%20Russia%20jammed%20GPS-guided%20munitions%20such%20as%20HIMARS%20and%20moved%20supply%20depots%20farther%20from%20the%20front%2C%20taking%20them%20out%20of%20rocket%20range%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20logistical%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20issue%20isn't%20military%20technology%2C%20which%20is%20inevitably%20nullified%20or%20copied%20by%20the%20other%20side%2C%20but%20adaptability%2C%20either%20in%20responsiveness%20to%20intelligence%20about%20the%20arrival%20of%20a%20new%20weapon%20or%20in%20changing%20tactics%20once%20that%20weapon%20is%20encountered%20in%20combat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20classic%20example%20is%20the%20Israel%20Defense%20Forces%20in%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%20in%20October%201973.%20In%20the%20first%20days%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20Israeli%20tanks%20were%20decimated%20when%20they%20recklessly%20charged%20Egyptian%20infantry%20units%20that%20were%20heavily%20armed%20with%20Russian-made%20Sagger%20anti-tank%20missiles%20and%20RPG-7%20anti-tank%20rockets.%20But%20within%20a%20week%2C%20the%20IDF%20adopted%20combined-arms%20teams%20of%20tanks%2C%20infantry%2C%20and%20artillery%2C%20which%20enabled%20Israeli%20tanks%20to%20operate%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20significant%20about%20the%20October%20strike%20on%20the%20Russian%20helicopter%20bases%20is%20that%20despite%20having%20ample%20warning%20about%20ATACMS%20and%20painful%20experience%20with%20Ukraine's%20other%20Western-made%20weapons%2C%20Russia%20did%20not%20protect%20its%20vital%20attack%20helicopters%2C%20which%20it%20could%20have%20moved%20to%20bases%20farther%20from%20the%20front%20rather%20than%20leaving%20them%20parked%20at%20exposed%20forward%20airfields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELearning%20the%20hard%20way%20from%20mistakes%20is%20an%20inevitable%20part%20of%20life.%20For%20Russia%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20way%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20a%20master's%20in%20political%20science.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22a48008f66dd60e4ae3cb2319a8aa10eb%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-dep