ea536d588dc55ccd378%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20at%20At-Tanf%20Garrison%20in%20Syria%20fire%20an%2081%20mm%20mortar%20during%20a%20readiness%20exercise%20on%20April%2022%2C%202020.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%2FStaff%20Sgt.%20William%20Howard%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIran-backed%20groups%20have%20launched%20dozens%20of%20attacks%20on%20US%20forces%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Syria%20since%20October%2017.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20drone%20and%20rocket%20strikes%20have%20injured%20a%20number%20of%20troops%2C%20but%20there's%20been%20little%20retaliation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMiddle%20East%20security%20experts%20say%20there%20are%20a%20number%20of%20reasons%20why%20the%20US%20is%20holding%20its%20fire.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20forces%20stationed%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20have%20endured%20a%20constant%20stream%20of%20attacks%20from%20Iran-backed%20groups%20over%20the%20past%20few%20weeks%2C%20violence%20that's%20parallel%20to%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20but%20nonetheless%20directly%20related%20to%20the%20bloody%20conflict.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20attacks%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Syria%20%E2%80%94%20mostly%20carried%20out%20using%20small%20drones%20and%20rockets%20%E2%80%94%20have%20injured%20dozens%20of%20American%20service%20members%2C%20but%20the%20US%20has%20chosen%20for%20the%20most%20part%20to%20avoid%20retaliation%20against%20the%20culprits.%20Middle%20East%20security%20experts%20say%20that's%20because%20Washington%20is%20walking%20a%20tightrope%2C%20balancing%20its%20own%20strategic%20interests%20in%20the%20region%20with%20avoiding%20escalation%20while%20also%20recognizing%20that%20its%20enemies%20are%20doing%20the%20same%2C%20trying%20to%20intentionally%20provoke%20it%20without%20taking%20it%20too%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20policymakers%20are%20%26quot%3Blooking%20at%20their%20strategic%20objectives%20in%20the%20region%20and%20understand%20that%20adversaries%20are%20trying%20to%20pull%20us%20off%20of%20those%20or%20make%20those%20fail%2C%20including%20in%20the%20context%20of%20luring%20us%20into%20these%20side%20conflicts%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonathan%20Lord%2C%20a%20former%20political%20military%20analyst%20at%20the%20Pentagon%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttacks%20on%20US%20forces%20by%20Iran-backed%20groups%20in%20the%20region%20are%20not%20a%20new%20phenomenon.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-allies-stuck-violent-cycle-iran-backed-militias-want-blood-2023-4%5C%22%3EDeadly%20exchanges%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20happening%20for%20decades%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20Iran's%20longstanding%20desire%20to%20expel%20the%20US%20from%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Between%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20inauguration%20in%20January%202021%20and%20April%202023%2C%20Iranian%20proxy%20forces%20carried%20out%2083%20attacks%20alone%2C%20a%20US%20Central%20Command%20(CENTCOM)%20spokesperson%20previously%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0But%20attacks%20are%20occurring%20more%20frequently%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20wave%20of%20attacks%2C%20widely%20described%20by%20US%20officials%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Buptick%2C%26quot%3B%20began%20amid%20swelling%20anger%20throughout%20the%20region%20over%20Israel's%20war%20against%20Hamas%20and%20its%20bombardment%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20a%20response%20to%20the%20October%207%20terror%20attacks%20perpetrated%20by%20Hamas%20against%20Israel.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtoninstitute.org%2Fpolicy-analysis%2Fprofile-islamic-resistance-iraq%5C%22%3EIslamic%20Resistance%20in%20Iraq%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20an%20umbrella%20term%20describing%20the%20recent%20operations%20that%20Iran-backed%20militias%20have%20conducted%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Syria%2C%20has%20claimed%20responsibility%20for%20the%20attacks%20against%20US%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Pentagon%20spokesperson%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20since%20October%2017%2C%20there%20have%20been%2040%20total%20attacks%20on%20US%20forces%20stationed%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Syria.%20Independent%20analyses%20from%20various%20think%20tanks%2C%20including%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtoninstitute.org%2Fpolicy-analysis%2Ftracking-anti-us-strikes-iraq-and-syria-during-gaza-crisis%5C%22%3EWashington%20Institute%20for%20Near%20East%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.understandingwar.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Firan-update-november-7-2023%5C%22%3EInstitute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20peg%20the%20figure%20slightly%20higher%20than%20what%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20revealed%20publicly%20because%20they%20use%20more%20inclusive%20methods%20for%20collecting%20the%20data.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225218%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20soldier%20is%20seen%20at%20a%20military%20base%20north%20of%20Baghdad%2C%20Iraq%2C%20on%20August%2023%2C%202020.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654bd38036d588dc55cd37a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223479%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20soldier%20is%20seen%20at%20a%20military%20base%20north%20of%20Baghdad%2C%20Iraq%2C%20on%20August%2023%2C%202020.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FThaier%20Al-Sudani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attacks%20have%20left%20at%20least%2046%20service%20members%20wounded%2C%20including%2025%20with%20traumatic%20brain%20injuries%2C%20Sabrina%20Singh%2C%20the%20deputy%20Pentagon%20press%20secretary%2C%20told%20reporters.%20She%20argued%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhile%20we%20see%20these%20attacks%20increase%2C%20we're%20not%20seeing%20significant%20casualties%20or%20significant%20harm%20to%20our%20service%20members.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat's%20been%20the%20US%20response%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20has%20only%20publicly%20confirmed%20a%20single%20incident%20of%20retaliation%20against%20the%20Iran-backed%20militias.%20Defense%20Secretary%20Lloyd%20Austin%20said%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FReleases%2FRelease%2FArticle%2F3570798%2Fsecretary-of-defense-lloyd-j-austin-iiis-statement-on-us-military-strikes-in-ea%2F%5C%22%3EOctober%2026%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20military%20conducted%20%26quot%3Bself-defense%20strikes%26quot%3B%20against%20facilities%20in%20Syria%20that%20were%20used%20by%20Iran's%20Islamic%20Revolutionary%20Guard%20Corps%20(IRGC)%20and%20its%20affiliated%20groups.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20nearly%20two%20weeks%20later%2C%20the%20attacks%20on%20American%20assets%20have%20not%20let%20up.%20At%20Tuesday's%20media%20briefing%2C%20reporters%20pressed%20Singh%20on%20whether%20US%20deterrence%20was%20working%20and%20if%20the%20late-October%20strikes%20had%20achieved%20anything.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20responded%20that%20the%20US%20decides%20when%20are%20where%20it%20wants%20to%20retaliate%2C%20and%20that%20there%20doesn't%20need%20to%20be%20a%20tit-for-tat%20exchange%20of%20firepower%20or%20comparative%20action%20every%20time%20there's%20an%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20incredibly%20strategic%20about%20when%20we%20decide%20to%20take%20kinetic%20action%2C%20and%20you%20saw%20that%20on%20October%2026%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20how%20successful%20we%20can%20be%20about%20damaging%20and%20destroying%20infrastructure%20that%20they%20have%20used%20too%2C%20and%20that's%20exactly%20what%20we%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20deeper%20level%2C%20Middle%20East%20security%20experts%20say%20the%20US%20knows%20it's%20not%20worth%20it%20to%20engage%20the%20militias%20at%20this%20moment%2C%20in%20part%20because%20escalation%20could%20send%20the%20entire%20region%20spiraling%20into%20utter%20chaos.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20the%20US%2C%20you've%20made%20a%20decision%20that%20under%20normal%20circumstances%2C%20if%20these%20militias%20were%20flicking%20little%20matches%20at%20us%2C%20we'd%20flick%20two%20matches%20back%20every%20so%20often%20just%20because%20we%20don't%20want%20Americans%20to%20get%20killed%2C%26quot%3B%20Michael%20Knights%2C%20the%20co-founder%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtoninstitute.org%2Fpolicy-analysis%2Fseries%2Fmilitia-spotlight%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitia%20Spotlight%3C%2Fa%3E%20platform%20at%20the%20Washington%20Institute%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22American%20soldiers%20stand%20during%20a%20joint%20exercise%20with%20Syrian%20Democratic%20Forces%20at%20the%20countryside%20of%20Deir%20Ezzor%20in%20northeastern%20Syria%2C%20Wednesday%2C%20Dec.%208%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d2669b20f1cf0019cd21e5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerican%20soldiers%20stand%20during%20a%20joint%20exercise%20with%20Syrian%20Democratic%20Forces%20at%20the%20countryside%20of%20Deir%20Ezzor%20in%20northeastern%20Syria%2C%20Wednesday%2C%20Dec.%208%2C%202021.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FBaderkhan%20Ahmad%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWeirdly%2C%20under%20these%20circumstances%2C%20we%20are%20saying%2C%20'Listen%2C%20we're%20sitting%20on%20a%20powder%20keg%20that's%20under%20everyone's%20house%2C%20and%20it%20doesn't%20matter%20if%20they%20flick%20matches%20at%20us%2C%20we're%20not%20going%20to%20flick%20matches%20back%20at%20them%20because%20we%20are%20not%20that%20irresponsible%2C%26quot%3B%20Knights%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20underlying%20fear%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%20is%20that%20the%20war%20with%20Hamas%20could%20expand%20into%20a%20regional%20conflict%2C%20drawing%20in%20Iran%20or%20its%20proxies%20in%20a%20more%20direct%20role.%20To%20some%20extent%2C%20this%20is%20already%20the%20case.%20Lebanon's%20Hezbollah%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-gearing-up-ground-invasion-war-with-hamas-risks-expanding-2023-10%5C%22%3Eregularly%20exchanges%20fire%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20Israeli%20military%2C%20Houthi%20rebels%20in%20Yemen%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-missile-ships-us-combat-power-red-sea-iran-attacks-2023-11%5C%22%3Elaunched%20missiles%20and%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20southern%20Israel%2C%20and%20the%20Islamic%20Resistance%20in%20Iraq%20continues%20to%20attack%20American%20assets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Biden%20administration%20also%20appears%20to%20be%20looking%20at%20these%20attacks%20and%20choosing%20to%20ignore%20them%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20because%20it's%20not%20necessarily%20seeing%20a%20strong%20push%20by%20the%20militias%20to%20inflict%20maximum%20causalities%20on%20US%20forces%20or%20overwhelm%20their%20defensive%20systems%2C%20Knights%20said.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20these%20groups%20are%20not%20trying%20their%20hardest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Israel's%20war%20with%20Hamas%2C%20such%20attacks%20might%20realistically%20only%20lead%20to%20a%20localized%20tit-for-tat%20exchange%20of%20firepower%2C%20like%20what%20happened%20in%20March%20after%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-defenses-werent-working-right-iranian-drone-killed-american-syria-2023-3%3Finline-endstory-related-recommendations%3D%5C%22%3EAmerican%20contractor%20was%20killed%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20an%20Iranian%20drone%20hit%20a%20base%20in%20Syria.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20this%20circumstance%2C%26quot%3B%20Knights%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20could%20trip%20off%20a%20Hezbollah-Iran-Israel%20war.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20high-stakes%20balancing%20act%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEscalation%20against%20US%20forces%20doesn't%20work%20on%20a%20binary%20scale%20where%20all%20of%20the%20sudden%20these%20groups%20just%20decide%20to%20go%20all%20in%20on%20attacks%2C%20said%20Lord%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%20Security%20prog