uels%E2%80%AFin%202030%E2%80%AFthan%20necessary%20to%20limit%20warming%20to%201.5%C2%B0C%2C%20according%20to%20a%20UN%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Fresources%2Fproduction-gap-report-2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20published%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20November%208.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%2C%20the%20report%20says%2C%20leads%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnear-term%20increase%E2%80%9D%20in%20coal%20production%2C%20followed%20by%20Indonesia%2C%20and%20Russia.%20The%20report%20also%20noted%20that%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%20being%20planned%20by%2012%20countries%20with%20the%20lowest%20levels%20of%20relative%20economic%20dependence%20on%20their%20production%20%E2%80%93%20including%20India%20%E2%80%93%20would%20exceed%20global%20levels%20under%20the%20respective%201.5%C2%B0C%20consistent%20pathways%20by%202040.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFossil%20fuels%20all%20the%20way%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20extreme%20weather%20events%20%E2%80%93%20heat%20waves%2C%20wildfires%20and%20glacial%20retreats%20%E2%80%93%20become%20more%20frequent%20and%20intense%2C%20the%20science%20is%20clear%3A%20the%20world%20has%20to%20limit%20global%20warming%20to%20under%201.5%C2%B0C%20or%2C%20at%20the%20least%2C%20to%202%C2%B0C%2C%20to%20tackle%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20The%20combustion%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20coal%20and%20gas%20%E2%80%93%20is%20the%20main%20source%20of%20carbon%20emissions%20that%20contribute%20to%20global%20warming%20and%20lead%20to%20climate%20change.%20Taking%20cognisance%20of%20this%2C%20countries%20and%20governments%20are%20pledging%20to%20decrease%20their%20production%2C%20use%20and%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuel-based%20energy%20and%20instead%20turn%20to%20cleaner%20energy%20sources%20such%20as%20solar%20and%20wind%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20promises%20are%20not%20always%20kept%2C%20and%20the%C2%A0United%20Nations%20Environment%20Programme%20(UNEP)%E2%80%99s%20annual%20Production%20Gap%20report%20tracks%20the%20misalignment%20between%20governments%E2%80%99%20planned%20fossil%20fuel%20production%20and%20global%20production%20levels%20consistent%20with%20limiting%20global%20warming%20to%201.5%C2%B0C%20or%202%C2%B0C.%20The%202023%20Production%20Gap%20Report%20is%20the%20fourth%20of%20its%20kind%2C%20and%20more%20than%2080%20researchers%20from%20over%2030%20countries%20contributed%20to%20the%20analysis%20and%20review%2C%20spanning%20numerous%20universities%2C%20think%20tanks%20and%20other%E2%80%AFresearch%20organisations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Fresources%2Fproduction-gap-report-2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20says%20the%20global%20production%20gap%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20steps%20governments%20have%20pledged%20to%20take%20to%20reduce%20dependence%20on%20fossil%20fuels%20and%20their%20actions%20to%20really%20do%20so%20%E2%80%93%20has%20remained%20%E2%80%9Clargely%20unchanged%E2%80%9D%20since%20the%20UN%20first%20assessed%20it%20in%202019.%20Governments%20across%20the%20world%20plan%20to%20produce%E2%80%AFaround%E2%80%AF110%25%20more%E2%80%AFfossil%20fuels%E2%80%AFin%202030%E2%80%AFthan%20would%20be%20in%20line%20with%20limiting%20warming%20to%201.5%C2%B0C%2C%E2%80%AFand%2069%25%20more%20than%20would%20be%20consistent%20with%202%C2%B0C%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20major%20fossil-fuel-producing%20governments%20are%20still%20planning%20near-term%20increases%20in%20coal%20production%20and%20long-term%20increases%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20is%20%E2%80%9Ccreating%20increasingly%20large%20production%20gaps%20over%20time%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20recommended%20that%20governments%20be%20more%20%E2%80%9Ctransparent%20in%20their%20plans%2C%20projections%2C%20and%20support%20for%20fossil%20fuel%20production%20and%20how%20they%20align%20with%20national%20and%20international%20climate%20goals%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%2C%20per%20the%20report%2C%20leads%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnear-term%20increase%E2%80%9D%20in%20coal%20production%20as%20it%20%E2%80%9Cseeks%20self-reliance%20and%20views%20the%20coal%20industry%20as%20currently%20being%20of%20paramount%20importance%20for%20income%20and%20employment%20generation%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20noted%20that%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%20being%20planned%20by%2012%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20Australia%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Canada%2C%20China%2C%20Colombia%2C%20India%2C%20Indonesia%2C%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Nigeria%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20with%20the%20lowest%20levels%20of%20relative%20economic%20dependence%20on%20their%20production%20would%20exceed%20global%20levels%20under%20the%20respective%201.5%C2%B0C-consistent%20pathways%20by%202040.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPer%20the%20report%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccountries%20should%20aim%20for%20a%20near%20total%20phase-out%20of%20coal%20production%20and%20use%20by%202040%20and%20a%20combined%20reduction%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%20and%20use%20by%20three-quarters%20by%202050%20from%202020%20levels%2C%20at%20a%20minimum%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CGovernments%20are%20literally%20doubling%20down%20on%20fossil%20fuel%20production%3B%20that%20spells%20double%20trouble%20for%20people%20and%20%5Bthe%5D%20planet%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20UN%20secretary-general%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20address%20climate%20catastrophe%20without%20tackling%20its%20root%20cause%3A%20fossil%20fuel%20dependence.%20COP28%20must%20send%20a%20clear%20signal%20that%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20age%20is%20out%20of%20gas%20%E2%80%94%20that%20its%20end%20is%20inevitable.%20We%20need%20credible%20commitments%20to%20ramp%20up%20renewables%2C%20phase%20out%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20and%20boost%20energy%20efficiency%2C%20while%20ensuring%20a%20just%2C%20equitable%20transition.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01203806%2Fpexels-marcin-jozwiak-3641377.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01203806%2Fpexels-marcin-jozwiak-3641377.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01203806%2Fpexels-marcin-jozwiak-3641377-300x158.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01203806%2Fpexels-marcin-jozwiak-3641377-1024x539.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683028%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22632%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Marcin%20Jozwiak%2FPexels%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20stand%20and%20peaking%20emissions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%2C%20in%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funfccc.int%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FNDC%2F2022-08%2FIndia%2520Updated%2520First%2520Nationally%2520Determined%2520Contrib.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eupdated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Nationally%20Determined%20Contributions%20submitted%20to%20the%20UNFCCC%20last%20year%20pledged%2C%20among%20others%2C%20to%20reduce%20the%20emissions%20intensity%20of%20its%20GDP%20by%2045%25%20by%202030%20(from%20the%202005%20levels)%2C%20to%20achieve%20about%2050%25%20of%20its%20cumulative%20electric%20power%20installed%20capacity%20from%20non-fossil%20fuel-based%20energy%20resources%20by%202030%20and%20to%20create%20an%20additional%20carbon%20sink%20of%202.5%20to%203%20billion%20tonnes%20of%20CO2%20equivalent%20through%20additional%20forest%20and%20tree%20cover%20by%202030.%20These%20steps%2C%20India%20held%2C%20would%20help%20the%20country%20reach%20its%20long-term%20goal%20of%20reaching%20net%20zero%20by%202070.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20has%20held%20%E2%80%93%20including%20at%20global%20forums%20such%20as%20the%20Conference%20of%20Parties%20(COP)%20%E2%80%93%20that%20even%20though%20it%20is%20among%20the%20top%20countries%20that%20produce%20the%20highest%20carbon%20emissions%20currently%2C%20the%20historical%20emissions%20of%20developing%20countries%20are%20low%20when%20compared%20to%20those%20of%20developed%20countries.%20Therefore%2C%20a%20phase%20%E2%80%98down%E2%80%99%20of%20coal%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20phase%20out%20%E2%80%93%20a%20total%20stop%20to%20coal%20production%20and%20use%20%E2%80%93%20is%20more%20feasible%2C%20just%20and%20equitable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExperts%20too%20have%20backed%20this%20stand%2C%20for%20coal%20is%20still%20essential%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20economic%20growth.%20Coal%20currently%20accounts%20for%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20electricity%20generation%2C%20and%20India%20needs%20it%20to%20lift%20millions%20out%20of%20poverty%2C%20experts%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscience.thewire.in%2Fexternal-affairs%2Fworld%2Fcop26-india-coal-phase-down-necessary-just-transition%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etold%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%20Science%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20developing%20countries%20are%20continuing%20their%20fossil%20fuel%20push%20as%20well.%20According%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimateactiontracker.org%2Fdocuments%2F1144%2FCAT_2023-06-08_Briefing_PhaseOutOilGas.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erecent%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20June%20by%20Climate%20Action%20Tracker%2C%20developed%20countries%20such%20as%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%2C%20Norway%20and%20Australia%20%E2%80%93%20the%20major%20oil%20and%20gas%20producers%20and%20exporters%20%E2%80%93%20are%20planning%20to%20expand%20their%20production%20and%20export%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20Though%20many%20governments%20have%20pledged%20to%20eliminate%20fossil%20fuel%20subsidies%2C%20this%20still%20has%20not%20taken%20place.%20And%20none%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20fossil%20fuel%20producers%20have%20committed%20to%20ending%20new%20investments%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%3B%20instead%2C%20they%20are%20increasing%20them%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20upcoming%20COP28%2C%20India%20hopes%20to%20push%20developed%20nations%20to%20become%20carbon%20negative%20rather%20than%20carbon%20neutral%20by%202050%20%E2%80%93%20so%20that%20this%20will%20permit%20developing%20countries%20more%20time%20to%20use%20fossil%20fuels%20for%20development%20needs%2C%20government%20sources%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fsci-tech%2Fenergy-and-environment%2Findia-to-push-developed-nations-to-become-carbon-negative-before-2050-report%2Farticle67419863.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etold%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Reuters.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20right%20to%20call%20out%20the%20hypocrisy%20of%20the%20developed%20world%20by%20insisting%20on%20a%20comprehensive%20fossil%20fuel%20phase%20out%20that%20includes%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%E2%80%9D%20commented%20Ashish%20Fernandes%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Climate%20Risk%20Horizons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20India%20cannot%20keep%20using%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20hypocrisy%20to%20hide%20its%20own%20abject%20failure%20to%20rein%20in%20the%20growth%20of%20coal%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CRenewable%20energy%20is%20the%20cheapest%20new%20source%20of%20electricity%20in%20India%2C%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20battery%20and%20other%20storage%20is%20also%20falling%20fast%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%E2%80%9CClimate%20Risk%20Horizons%E2%80%99%20analysis%20has%20shown%20in%20numerous%20states%20across%20the%20country%20that%20scrapping%20plans%20for%20new%20coal%20and%20even%20retiring%20some%20expensive%20coal%20plants%20while%20doubling%20down%20on%20renewables%20will%20lead%20to%20immense%20savings%20for%20the%20power%20system%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20benefitting%20state%20governments%20and%20consumers.%20There%20is%20no%20economic%20or%20financial%20rationale%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20new%20coal%20power%20plants%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20renewable%20energy%20is%20more%20than%20able%20to%20meet%20increased%20demand%20if%20the%20right%20policies%20are%20enacted.%20The%20public%20investment%20that%20is%20meant%20to%20go%20to%20new%20coal%20would%20be%20more%20productive%20if%20spent%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20underfunded%20energy%20transition.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20coal%20production%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%20As%20per%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1974359%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20Coal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20India%20has%20achieved%20%E2%80%9Ca%20notable%20upswing%E2%80%9D%20in%20overall%20coal%20production%20during%20October%202023%2C%20reaching%2078.65%20million%20tonnes%20(MT)%2C%20surpassing%20the%20figures%20of%2066.32%20MT%20in%20October%202022.%20That%20is%20an%20increase%20of%2018.59%25.%20The%20production%20of%20Coal%20India%20Limited%20(CIL)%20alone%20has%20increased%20to%2061.07%20MT%20in%20October%20this%20year%20as%20compared%20to%2052.94%20MT%20in%20October%202022%2C%20a%20growth%20of%2015.36%25.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20production%20of%20coking%20coal%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20used%20in%20the%20steel%20manufacturing%20industry%20%E2%80%93%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1953162%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexpected%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20reach%20140%20MT%20by%202030.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20few%20days%20ago%2C%20more%20than%2046%20million%20healthcare%20professionals%20from%20around%20the%20world%20wrote%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcop28healthletter.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eletter%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20COP28%20president-designate%2C%20calling%20on%20all%20countries%20to%20commit%20to%20%E2%80%9Caccelerating%20the%20phase-out%E2%80%9D%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20a%20just%20and%20equitable%20way%20due%20to%20its%20impacts%20on%20health%20and%20its%20role%20in%20climate%20change%20that%20also%20leads%20to%20the%20loss%20of%20human%20lives%20and%20endangerment%20of%20the%20environment.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699453757000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08194600%2Flachlan-dn8SEqz-7Rc-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fphase-out-phase-down-fossil-fuel-production-to-continue-unep-production-gap%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20year's%20edition%20of%20UNEP%E2%80%99s%20Production%20Gap%20report%20shows%20that%20governments%20worldwide%20plan%20to%20produce%20double%20the%20fossil%20fuels%20in%202030%20than%20the%201.5%C2%B0C%20global%20warming%20limit%20allows.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fphase-out-phase-down-fossil-fuel-production-to-continue-unep-production-gap%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hamas%20Attacked%20Israel%20Over%20Jerusalem%20Mosque%2C%20Once%20Freed%20By%20Indian%20Soldiers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EJust%20before%20sunrise%20on%20October%207%2C%20hundreds%20of%20Hamas%20operatives%20crossed%20Gaza's%20border%20with%20Israel.%20Within%20minutes%2C%20they%20poured%20across%2C%20opening%20the%20gates%20of%20hell.%20On%20that%20morning%2C%20neither%20the%20Israeli%20soldiers%20monitoring%20the%20Gaza%20border%20nor%20the%20civilians%20living%20in%20nearby%20towns%20and%20kibbutz%20had%20any%20idea%20about%20the%20bloodiest%20attack%20in%20the%20country's%2075-year%20history.%20Hamas%20called%20it%20'Operation%20Al-Aqsa%20Flood'%2C%20in%20reference%20to%20the%20mosque%20in%20Jerusalem's%20Old%20City%20that%20houses%20the%20third%20holiest%20site%20in%20Islam.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHamas%20said%20the%20attack%20was%20carried%20out%20in%20reference%20to%20the%20police%20storming%20the%20mosque%20in%202022.%20The%20mosque%20is%20situated%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20which%20is%20over%204%2C000%20kilometres%20away%20from%20India%20yet%20has%20a%20connect%20with%20our%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20100%20years%20ago%2C%20during%20the%20First%20World%20War%2C%20Indian%20soldiers%20helped%20win%20the%20city%20for%20the%20British%20who%20defeated%20the%20Ottoman%20Empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20million%20Indian%20soldiers%20fought%20for%20the%20British%20in%201917%20to%20liberate%20Jerusalem.%20Between%201914%20and%201918%2C%20they%20fought%20the%20Turkish-German%20armies%20at%20Gallipoli%2C%20the%20Suez%20Canal%2C%20through%20the%20Sinai%20and%20Palestine%20and%20finally%20Damascus%2C%20with%20crucial%20battles%20in%20Gaza%2C%20Jerusalem%2C%20Jaffa%2C%20Haifa%2C%20Nablus%20and%20Megiddo%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Fopinion%2Fremembering-the-indian-soldiers-who-helped-liberate-jerusalem-100-years-ago-498788%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJerusalem%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20cemetery%20in%20memory%20of%20Indian%20soldiers%20who%20died%20fighting%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndian%20soldiers%20also%20fought%20in%20the%20Battle%20of%20Tabsor%20during%20World%20War%20I.%20Fought%20on%20September%2019-20%2C%201918%2C%20it%20was%20an%20important%20battle%20and%20the%20opening%20of%20the%20famous%20Meggido%20offensive.%20These%20events%20played%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20the%20victory%20of%20the%20Entente%20Forces%20over%20the%20Ottoman%20armies%20in%20Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20soldiers%20who%20participated%20in%20this%20offensive%20were%20Indian%20troops%2C%20consisting%20of%20Punjabis%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Gurkhas%20and%20soldiers%20from%20various%20other%20regions%20of%20undivided%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20ago%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20unveiled%20a%20plaque%20at%20Ra'anana%20in%20northern%20Israel%20in%20the%20memory%20of%20these%20Indian%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699452180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fbq9dfrro_indian-soldiers-in-jerusalem_625x300_08_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhamas-attacked-israel-over-mosque-in-jerusalem-once-liberated-by-indian-soldiers-4557812%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Over%20100%20years%20ago%2C%20during%20the%20First%20World%20War%2C%20Indian%20soldiers%20helped%20win%20the%20city%20for%20the%20British%20who%20defeated%20the%20Ottoman%20Empire.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhamas-attacked-israel-over-mosque-in-jerusalem-once-liberated-by-indian-soldiers-4557812%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhamas-attacked-israel-over-mosque-in-jerusalem-once-liberated-by-indian-soldiers-4557812%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhamas-attacked-israel-over-mosque-in-jerusalem-once-liberated-by-indian-soldiers-4557812%2Famp%2F1%22%